			<ns0:name>jvo...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/102292187274959663599/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">The plugin takes a hash of bitcode to identify the bitcode content for translation caching.  However, it needs to verify that the hash is actually derived from the content before putting a nexe into the translation cache.

Previously there was a concern that adding this verification as the pexe is streamed in will add a dependency on chrome code, and that was bad because we DEPs'ed chrome back into NaCl.  Perhaps until the plugin is really moved to the renderer, the importing of code should still be done cleanly?  E.g., we could add a ppb_nacl_private interface to get access to the family of hash routines that we need, rather than access them directly.
